<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1273,1931]" box="[151,1032,1273,1298]" pageId="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1273,1298]" pageId="1">Description.</emphasis>
Length (including wings): male 
<quantity box="[664,802,1273,1298]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.55" metricValueMax="3.6" metricValueMin="3.5" pageId="1" unit="mm" value="3.55" valueMax="3.6" valueMin="3.5">3.5–3.6 mm</quantity>
; female 
<quantity box="[896,1028,1273,1298]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.65" metricValueMax="3.7" metricValueMin="3.6" pageId="1" unit="mm" value="3.65" valueMax="3.7" valueMin="3.6">3.6–3.7mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1273,1931]" pageId="1">
Body ochraceous. Face yellowish; gena with dark brown markings on lateral margin; apex of anteclypeus brownish; ocelli pink (
<figureCitation box="[405,469,1340,1365]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,244,1920,1942]" captionTargetBox="[191,1392,200,1854]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[191,1396,194,1895]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Philippogalla modesta A, habitus of male, dorsal view; B, habitus of male, lateral view; C, head and thorax of male, dorsal view; D, face of male; E, forewing of male; F, habitus of female, dorsal view; G, habitus of female, lateral view; H, head and thorax of female, dorsal view; I, face of female; J, first valvulae; K, second valvulae; L, apex of first valvulae; M, apex of second valvulae; N, female genitalia, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/829349/files/figure.png" pageId="1">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
D). Pronotum brownish with dense yellowish spots (
<figureCitation box="[1062,1126,1340,1365]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,244,1920,1942]" captionTargetBox="[191,1392,200,1854]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[191,1396,194,1895]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Philippogalla modesta A, habitus of male, dorsal view; B, habitus of male, lateral view; C, head and thorax of male, dorsal view; D, face of male; E, forewing of male; F, habitus of female, dorsal view; G, habitus of female, lateral view; H, head and thorax of female, dorsal view; I, face of female; J, first valvulae; K, second valvulae; L, apex of first valvulae; M, apex of second valvulae; N, female genitalia, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/829349/files/figure.png" pageId="1">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
C). Mesoscutum with basal triangles brownish. Forewing transparent, with brownish median transverse band, apex brown, costal margin yellow, veins brownish and yellow (
<figureCitation box="[556,619,1406,1431]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,244,1920,1942]" captionTargetBox="[191,1392,200,1854]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[191,1396,194,1895]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Philippogalla modesta A, habitus of male, dorsal view; B, habitus of male, lateral view; C, head and thorax of male, dorsal view; D, face of male; E, forewing of male; F, habitus of female, dorsal view; G, habitus of female, lateral view; H, head and thorax of female, dorsal view; I, face of female; J, first valvulae; K, second valvulae; L, apex of first valvulae; M, apex of second valvulae; N, female genitalia, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/829349/files/figure.png" pageId="1">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
E).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1273,1931]" pageId="1">
Style apical half straight. Connective with broad anterior projection. Aedeagal preatrium straight, longer than shaft; dorsal apodeme triangular in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[695,771,1473,1498]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,244,1985,2007]" captionTargetBox="[193,1417,207,1938]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[167,1429,191,1975]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Philippogalla modesta A, male pygofer, anal tube and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, connective, ventral view; C, connective, lateral view; D, aedeagus, lateral view; E, aedeagus, ventral view; F, style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/829353/files/figure.png" pageId="1">Figs. 3</figureCitation>
D–E).
</paragraph>
